  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]&nbsp;</span><strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>pork mince</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3 min or until starting to brown, breaking it up as you go</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, drain and rinse the <strong>black beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/525.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/525.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/525.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/525.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/525.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chipotle paste</strong>, <strong>cumin</strong> and crumble in the <strong>stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, stirring well to combine</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>rice</strong> and stir to coat the grains</p>\r\n<p>Add&nbsp;350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span>&nbsp;water and the drained <strong>black beans</strong> and bring to the boil covered with a lid over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/525.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/525.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/525.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/525.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/525.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low, cover with a lid and cook for 10-15 min or until the water has absorbed and the rice is tender</p>\r\n<p>Tip: add a splash or two of water if the rice looks too dry</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/525.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/525.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/525.-step-3-x700.jpg",
